T*
(The morning of April 12, 1981, 20 years to the day after Yuri Gagarin became the first person) Tj
T*
(in space, the Space Shuttle thundered into the Florida sky. Commander Young and Pilot Crippen) Tj
T*
(were at the controls as the Shuttle ascended on its first flight. But the launch, like much of) Tj
T*
(the flight, was really under the control of four computers in the avionics bays one deck below) Tj
T*
(the crew. A fifth computer stood ready to take over in case of a catastrophic computer) Tj
T*
(malfunction. These computers, Model AP-101B, were part of IBM's System/4 Pi family. The Space) Tj
T*
(Shuttle AP-101B computer. This unit flew on multiple flights, including STS-38 \(1990\) and) Tj
T*
(STS-40 \(1001\). Photo courtesy of RR Auction . Introduced around 1967, the System/4 Pi family) Tj
T*
(was a line of compact, powerful computers designed for avionics roles. The military used these) Tj
T*
(computers in everything from the F-4 fighter and B-52 bomber to submarine sonar systems and the) Tj
T*
(Harpoon anti-ship missile. Other computers in the System/4 Pi family played more peaceful roles) Tj
T*
(in the development of GPS and fly-by-wire flight controls. In space, System/4 Pi computers) Tj
