T*
(Source: Andrew Nesbitt | Published: 2026-03-29T10:00:00+00:00) Tj
T*
(Link: https://nesbitt.io/2026/03/29/the-roles-of-packages.html) Tj
T*
(Greg Wilson?s recent post An E-Bike for the Mind reminded me of Jorma Sajaniemi?s work on the) Tj
T*
(roles of variables. Sajaniemi found that just eleven roles cover nearly all variables in novice) Tj
T*
(programs: stepper, most-wanted holder, gatherer, one-way flag, and so on. As Wilson puts it,) Tj
T*
(types tell you about a variable?s state at rest while roles tell you about its state in motion.) Tj
T*
(Once you learn the roles, you can look at unfamiliar code and immediately recognize the shape) Tj
T*
(of the algorithm from how data flows through it. Every package in a registry plays a particular) Tj
T*
(role, whether it?s a library your application calls, a tool your build pipeline runs, a daemon) Tj
T*
(your infrastructure depends on, or a firmware blob that makes your hardware work. This holds) Tj
T*
(across all kinds of package managers, from npm and RubyGems to Homebrew, apt, Helm, Terraform) Tj
T*
(Registry, and OpenVSX, and the role tells you more about how a package fits into a system than) Tj
T*
(the name or the README. Two packages in completely different domains, managed by completely) Tj
T*
(different tools, can behave identically because they play the same role. Code execution) Tj
T*
(Application. neovim and ffmpeg via Homebrew, httpie via pip, VS Code exte...) Tj
