(Link: https://computer.rip/2026-03-29-telecheck-and-tyms-past.html) Tj
T*
(Years ago, when I was in college, I had one of those friends who never quite had it together.) Tj
T*
(You know the type; I'm talking lost a debit card and took three months to get a new one because) Tj
T*
(of some sort of "mixup" with the credit union that I think consisted mostly of not calling them) Tj
T*
(for three months. In the mean time, our mutual friend ended up in a quandry: at WalMart, at one) Tj
T*
(in the morning, with a $2 purchase and no cash. Well, this was no problem for that particular) Tj
T*
(space case: he had his checkbook. If you think about it, it's actually pretty remarkable that) Tj
T*
(grocery stores accept personal checks. It's a very high risk for of payment. Even if the check) Tj
T*
(is genuine, the customer could be writing it against an empty account. On top of that, with) Tj
T*
(modern printers and the declining use of MICR, forging checks is trivial. When you offer a) Tj
T*
(check, the retailer has very little to go on to decide whether or not you're good for the) Tj
T*
(money. Surely, fraud must run out of hand?and yet, just about every major grocer still accepts) Tj
T*
(personal checks. Retail point-of-sale acceptance of personal checks is the product of an) Tj
T*
(intriguing industry that handles all the challenges of checks at once: a comb...) Tj
T*
() Tj
ET
